title: Nonconvex great rhombicosidodecahedron
summary: In geometry, the nonconvex great rhombicosidodecahedron is a nonconvex uniform polyhedron, indexed as U67. It has 62 faces (20 triangles, 30 squares and 12 pentagrams), 120 edges, and 60 vertices.[1] It is also called the quasirhombicosidodecahedron.
